<p>17 May 1915<br/>Monday</p>
<p>More big shells   &amp;  a whole lot of shrapnel during the day but very few hit<br/>It is very droll to pick up a Sydney newspaper about a month old   &amp;  read about the   <strike>it</strike> Turks being short of men   &amp;  munitions   &amp;  then listen to the shells bursting about every five minutes</p>
<p>1915 May 18<br/>Tuesday</p>
<p>More sapping   &amp;  repairing Head &ndash; Quarters which has been damaged by the 8.5 in shells.<br/>The dad not at all well.</p>
